# Klikcy ‚Äî Awwwards Rank #1 Design System (Shipped)

This rule replaces prior generic ‚Äúaward-winning‚Äù guidance for **this codebase only**. It records what is implemented so future edits stay coherent.

## Visual concept (one sentence)

**‚ÄúSignal Mesh‚Äù** ‚Äî a near-black editorial canvas where cyan/teal gradients read as live signal on a grain-textured mesh, Syne headlines feel like instrumentation, and motion choreographs attention without obscuring the offer.

## Color & theme tokens

- **Light & dark** use semantic HSL variables in `:root` and `html[data-theme="dark"]` (mirrored with `html.dark` for Tailwind `dark:`). Source of truth: `src/styles/globals.css`.
- **Brand hues** stay within teal/cyan + navy (primary / ink / void) ‚Äî max three chromatic families plus neutrals.
- **Mesh layers** use `--c-mesh-1`, `--c-mesh-2`, `--c-mesh-3` radial stacks on `--ink` base (see `.mesh-bg-layer`).
- **Grain** is a fixed full-viewport `body::after` SVG turbulence overlay (`--grain-opacity`).

Toggle theme via `ThemeRoot` / `applyTheme()` ‚Äî never set colors ad hoc in JSX.

## Typography

- **Display:** Syne Variable (`@fontsource-variable/syne`) ‚Äî `var(--font-display)`.
- **Body:** DM Sans 400/500/700 (`@fontsource/dm-sans/*`) ‚Äî `var(--font-body)`.
- **Scale:** All fluid sizes use `clamp()` custom properties: `--type-display`, `--type-h1`, `--type-h2`, `--type-h3`, `--type-body`, `--type-body-lg`, `--type-label`, `--type-eyebrow`.
- **Utility:** `font-display` class maps to Syne; Tailwind `font-sans` / `font-display` in `tailwind.config.ts` bind to the same CSS variables.

## Layout primitives

- **`k-container`** ‚Äî max width `var(--container-max)` + `var(--space-gutter)` horizontal padding (`globals.css`).
- **`container-x`** ‚Äî legacy shadcn layout width; `PageSection` defaults to `innerClassName ?? "container-x section"`. Override with `innerClassName="k-container section"` when aligning to the new marketing grid.
- **Asymmetry** ‚Äî homepage intentionally alternates split grids, sticky side columns, negative horizontal translation (`lg:-translate-x-[var(--container-bleed)]`), and full-bleed hero imagery.

## Motion & libraries

- **Lenis + GSAP:** `LenisGsapProvider` (`src/components/layout/LenisGsapProvider.tsx`) instantiates Lenis, proxies `document.documentElement` for `ScrollTrigger`, and drives `lenis.raf` on `gsap.ticker`. Disabled entirely when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.
- **ScrollTrigger:** Registered once in `src/lib/gsap.ts` via `ensureGsapPlugins()`.
- **Hero timeline:** `HomeHero` uses `gsap.context` + **SplitType** character stagger, timed to: background ‚Üí eyebrow (0.1s) ‚Üí chars (0.25s) ‚Üí subcopy (0.5s) ‚Üí CTA elastic (0.65s). Cleanup calls `split.revert()` + `ctx.revert()`.
- **Staggered reveals:** `StaggerReveal` animates `[data-reveal-item]` children on first enter (default 80ms stagger).
- **Count-up:** `HomeStatsRow` animates integers with `gsap.to` + `ScrollTrigger` `once: true`.
- **Pinned narrative:** `HomePinnedChapter` uses **CSS `position: sticky`** + scrubbed GSAP on the headline (no GSAP `pin` ‚Äî fewer Lenis conflicts).
- **Magnetic CTA:** `MagneticButton` wraps primary hero CTA; uses GSAP `to` on pointer move (fine pointer only).
- **Tilt cards:** `TiltCard` applies perspective rotate from pointer (fine pointer only).
- **Scramble nav:** `ScrambleLink` randomises label characters on hover/focus (`DesktopScrambleNav`).
- **Custom cursor:** `CustomCursor` ‚Äî dot + lerped ring; disabled on coarse pointers and reduced motion.
- **Route wipe:** `PageTransition` scales a fixed overlay on `location.pathname` change (skipped on first paint / reduced motion).

**Rule:** any new GSAP work must run inside `gsap.context(() => { ... }, scopeRef)` and revert on unmount.

## Performance

- **Fonts:** Self-hosted via Fontsource; no Google Fonts `<link>` in `index.html`.
- **Hero image:** WebP at `public/hero-klikcy.webp` with `<link rel="preload">` in `index.html` and `fetchPriority="high"` on the `<img>`.
- **Below-fold images:** always `loading="lazy"` when added.
- **Bundle:** GSAP + Lenis + SplitType ship in the main chunk (~730kB gzipped ~227kB) ‚Äî acceptable for this marketing SPA; split further with `import()` only when a route truly isolates heavy motion.

## Content layer

- Marketing copy for the homepage lives in `src/content/home.ts` (including `homeFaqs`).
- `src/lib/home-content.ts` re-exports `homeFaqs` for JSON-LD and legacy imports.

## Component architecture

```
src/components/
  animations/   ScrambleLink, StaggerReveal
  layout/       LenisGsapProvider, ThemeRoot, ThemeToggle, CustomCursor, PageTransition, PageSection
  sections/     HomeHero, HomePinnedChapter, HomeStatsRow
  service/      ServiceHero, ServiceStateHubs, ServiceMetroCities
  ui/           MagneticButton, TiltCard (+ existing shadcn primitives)
src/content/    home.ts (page copy)
src/hooks/      useReducedMotion, useMediaQuery, useMousePosition
src/lib/        gsap.ts (plugin registration)
src/styles/     globals.css (design tokens + grain + cursor + page transition)
src/utils/      cn.ts, math.ts, device.ts
```

## Accessibility

- One **h1** on the homepage (`HomeHero`).
- Skip link retained in `Header`.
- Enhanced `:focus-visible` in `globals.css`.
- Mobile navigation is a **full-screen overlay** with **no accordion** (flat scroll + grouped links).
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for Lenis, cursor, and GSAP-driven sections.

## Extending consistently

1. Add copy to `src/content/home.ts` (or a new file under `src/content/`), not inside presentation components.
2. Add or adjust CSS variables in `globals.css`; avoid raw hex in TSX except for one-off SVG data-URLs.
3. New animated section: wrap in a ref-scoped `gsap.context`, prefer `ScrollTrigger` `once: true` unless scrub is part of the concept.
4. Use `cn()` from `src/utils/cn.ts` (also re-exported as `@/lib/utils`).
5. After layout-affecting changes with Lenis, call `ScrollTrigger.refresh()` if triggers misalign.

